###Two Pence

Three distinct settings are now believed to have been made. Mathews notes that at least 13 runs were made, but
it does not follow that adjustments were made between each print run. The Two Pence was probably printed
after the four pence, since errors exist with the 4 in corners, probably left on the cliche from the previous
run.

__First Printing__

Inverted 2 (No.16)

